<section class="oe_container">
    <div class="oe_row oe_spaced">
        <h2 class="oe_slogan">Two level discounts in Sales & Customer Invoice</h2>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="oe_container oe_dark">
    <div class="oe_row">
        <h2 class="oe_slogan">Sale order line form View</h2>
        <div class="oe_span6">
            <p class='oe_mt32'>
There is two discounts fields in which the first discount field discounts with the unit price. 
Then the discounted unit price again discounts with the second discount field.
            </p>
            <p class='oe_mt32'>
For example 8+2, this is not 10 but it is 8% discount then 2% discount after that. 
Let's say unit price is 100, then after first discount with 8% will become 92. Then 2% of 92 = 1.84 again discounts from 92.
So final unit price become 90.16 .
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="oe_span6">
            <div class="oe_bg_img">
                <img class="oe_picture oe_screenshot" src="sale_sc_01.png">
            </div>
        </div>
   </div>
</section>

<section class="oe_container">
    <h2 class="oe_slogan">sale order line tree view</h2>
    <div class="oe_row">
        <div class="oe_span6">
            <div class="oe_bg_img">
                <img class="oe_picture oe_screenshot" src="sale_sc_02.png">
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="oe_span6">
            <p class='oe_mt32'>
                Two discount fields Disc-I and Disc-II. Final unit price computed as mention above.
            </p>
            <p class='oe_mt32'>
                To get this feature, You have to enable in sales settings.
                Sale -> Settings -> Allow discounts on sale order line.
            </p>
        </div>
   </div>
</section>

<section class="oe_container oe_dark">
    <div class="oe_row">
        <h2 class="oe_slogan">Customer invoice form view</h2>
        <div class="oe_span6">
            <p class='oe_mt32'>
The same discounts from sale order line is mapped to customer invoice line.
            </p>
            <p class='oe_mt32'>
Even customer can directly use invoice instead of generating from sales order.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="oe_span6">
            <div class="oe_bg_img">
                <img class="oe_picture oe_screenshot" src="sale_sc_03.png">
            </div>
        </div>
   </div>
</section>

